Current total attendance is just over 63.5 Million, and the average attendance per game is 26,665 with 47 games left in the regular season. This would sum up to around 64.7 Million. Also, the wildcard games are not very close, so it is unlikely there would be any surprises in attendance in the remaining games.

Looking at online averages and other guesses shows that it would be between 60 and 65 million people. I also put a little in 65 and 70 million just incase some large event happens that cause it to go up more.

Attendance has trended downward each year from 2010 to 2019. 2019 had a total of 68.5mm. I've discounted 2021 due to lockdowns but that was a huge drop to around 45mm. Average attendance through 19 games is around 26K / game, 15 of the 30 teams will be hosting on any given game. 26K * 162 * 15=63MM. I could not find month by month historical average attendance figures that could impact my assumptions. Possible that early season generates the most buzz, which would make the 55-60mm look more attractive.
